complaint_detail: CALLER REPORTS THAT THE JANITORS OF THE SENIOR CITIZEN BUILDING ARE POURING DIRTY MOTOR OIL DOWN IN THE CITY SEWER.
inspection_log:
[INSPECTION LOG #: 1244 29-AUG-11 10:30:00] I RESPONDED TO A COMPLAINT THAT STATED A JANITOR WAS SEEN DUMPING OIL INTO THE SEWERS. UPON ARRIVAL, I SPOKE WITH THE BUILDING ENGINEER RANDY BURL AND EXPLAINED TO HIM THE REASON FOR MY VISIT. THE SUBJECT SITE IS A 200 ROOM SENIOR CITIZEN APARTMENT COMPLEX WITH AN EXTENSIVE PARKING LOT. MR. BURL INFORMED ME THAT NO ONE CHANGES OIL OR WORKS ON VEHICLES IN THE PARKING LOT AND FURTHERMORE HE SAID IT IS AGAINST THE RULES.


WE THEN CHECKED 3 SEWERS IN THE PARKING LOT. AT THIS TIME ALL 3 APPEARED TO BE FREE OF OIL.

THROWING BAGS OUT OF WINDOWS POSSIBLE ACM AND LEAD ISSUES.
inspection_log:
[INSPECTION LOG #: 3542 07-JUN-12 ] RECEIVED A PHONE MESSAGE ON MY WORK CELL PHONE FROM A PRIVATECITIZEN, WHO STATED THAT SHE WITNESSED WORKERS THROWING BLACK BAGS FROM THE UPPER FLOORS OR ROOF TO THE GRASSY KNOLL BELOW AND UNKNOWN DEBRIS. THIS ACTIVITY HAPPENED ON WEDNESDAY JUNE 06,2012 ACCORDING TO THE COMPLAINANT.SHE STATED THAT THE SCHOOL HAS ASBESTOS AND LEAD PAINT AND THAT THE SCHOOL IS OVER 100 YEARS OLD. SHE ALSO STATED THAT SHE CALLED IDPH IN SPRINGFIELD ILLINOIS WITH THE SAME CONCERNS. THIS COMPLAINT WAS LOGGED INTO HANSEN VIAEMAIL REQUEST BY INSPECTOR KAYNOT THROUGH THE COMPLAINANT AS ATTACHED BELOW.

I ARRIVED ON SITE AND INSPECTED THE OUT SIDE AREAS OF CONCERN. I WATCHED THE ACTIVITY FOR 5-10 MINUTES ON SEVERAL AREAS OUTSIDE AND WITNESSED NO WORKERS THROWING DEBRIS FROM FLOORS OR THE ROOF. THERE WERE SEVERAL AREAS OF ACTIVITY THAT INCLUDES GRINDING AND BRICK REPLACEMENT OF THE PARAPET WALL ON THE SOUTH AND WEST FACING ROOF LINES. THESE WORKERS WERE ON SWING STAGE SCAFFOLD IN A FENCED OFF REGULATED CONSTRUCTION AREA. IN THE SOUTH EAST PARKING LOT THERE WERE SEVERAL DUMPSTERS FOR THE ROOFING REPAIR STAGING AND A CRANE THAT WAS LOWERING GAYLORD TYPE TARPS WITH ROOF PEBBLES AND TAR DEBRIS INTO THE DUMPSTERS. NO EMISSIONS WERE WITNESSED. THERE WERE 2 MANLIFTS LOCATED AT THE BOILER ROOM CHIMNEY, DOING REPAIR TO THE BRICKS. NO EMISSION WERE WITNESSED THERE. I WENT INSIDE THE SCHOOL AND MET WITH THE LUNCHROOM MANAGER TESSY. I ASKED IF SHE COULDDIRECT ME TO THE ENGINEER OF THE SCHOOL. WHEN I ARRIVED BY THE BOILER ROOM, THERE WAS A MEETING ALREADY IN PROGRESS WITH THE ENGINEER KEITH SENEVEY, REP FROM CPS BOB CHISTOLIEB AND CHRIS SCOTT OF JACOBS, RICK KOCOUREK OF FH PACHEAN AND GLEN GARDNER IDPH ONSITE. WE SPOKE ABOUT THE COMPLAINT AND THE WORK THAT WAS ONGOING. PERMITS WERE PROVIDED FOR THE SCAFFOLDS AND BUILDING PERMITS. NO ASBESTOS OR LEAD WORK WAS GOING ON. THE ROOF WORK WAS GOING ON AS WELL AS THE WORK WITNESSED ON THE PARAPET AND CHIMNEY. THERE WAS NO VIOLATION ISSUED. I DID CALL THE COMPLAINANT BACK ON FRIDAY 6/8/2012 AND LEFT A MESSAGE TO EXPLAIN TO HER MY FINDINGS. SHE DID CALL BACK AND I EXPLAINED TO HER THAT MY INSPECTION OF HER COMPLAINT WAS UNFOUNDED AND THE WORK ONGOING DID NOT INCLUDE ACM OR LBP. SHE DID NOT LIKE MY REPLY AND BECAME UPSET AND LOUD.I REFERRED HER TO OTIS OMENAZU FOR FOLLOW UP. 

FROM: KAY, BARBARASENT: THURSDAY, JUNE 07, 2012 9:38 AMTO: JACKSON, KARENCC: OMENAZU, OTIS; SCHNOES, KEVINSUBJECT: FW: MARQUETTE ELEMENTARY SCHOOLHERE ARE THE TWO COMPLAINTI RECEIVED VIA PHONE AND EMAIL. IF YOU CAN PUT THEM IN I WOULD MUCH APPRECIATE THAT...BOTH CPS SCHOOL.

complaint_detail: ON AUGUST 22ND, 2013 A JOINT INSPECTION WAS CONDUCTED OF GROWING POWER, INC. LOCATED AT THE ABOVE ADDRESS. .
inspection_log:
[INSPECTION LOG #: 7025 22-AUG-13 12:15:00] THE INSPECTORS INCLUDED GEORGE HAIRSTON, JR., SENIOR ENVIRONMENTAL INSPECTOR; JOHN KRYL, DIRECTOR OF ENVIRONMENTAL INSPECTIONS; AND RENANTE MARANTE, ENGINEER III, PERMITTINGDIVISION,FROM THE CHICAGO DEPARTMENT OF PUBLIC HEALTH (CDPH), AND RICHARD FINLEY FROM THE ILLINOIS ENVIRONMENTAL PROTECTION AGENCY (IEPA). LAUREL SIMS IS IN CHARGE OF PRODUCTION AND MARKETING FOR GROWING POWER, INC. ERIKA ALLEN ((312) 735-4833), IS THE PROJECT DIRECTOR.BRIAN ELLIS IS A SITE SUPERVISOR. WE MET WITH BRIAN ELLIS AND LAUREL SIMS WHILE ON SITE. 


UPON ARRIVING FOR AN IEPA DEVELOPMENT PERMIT INSPECTION, WE FOUND THAT THE SITE HAD ALREADY BEGAN COMPOSTING WITHOUT THEIR IEPA OPERATING PERMIT, NOR THEIR CITY CLASS III PERMIT, FOR APPROXIMATELY THE LAST TWO MONTHS. LAUREL CLAIMED THAT SOMEONE FROM THE CDPH, WHO SHE COULDN'T NAME, HAD GIVEN THEM PERMISSION TO COMMENCE OPERATIONS WITHOUT THE NECESSARY PERMITS. 


THE COMPOSTING IS BEING CONDUCTED INSIDE A HOOP HOUSE, APPROXIMATELY20 FEET WIDE BY100 FEET LONG, AND 8 TO 10 FEET TALL. THE HOOP HOUSE CONSISTED OF A PLASTIC TARP STRETCHED OVER A METAL FRAME. AS THE FRONT AND BACK OF THE HOOP HOUSE WAS OPEN TO THE ELEMENTS, THE COMPOST OPERATION MAY NOT BE CONSIDERED ?IN-VESSEL? AS DEFINED IN CHAPTER 11-4-2510 OF THE CITY ORDINANCE. 


THE REAR OF THE SITE, BEHIND THE BUILDING, WAS COMPLETELY COVERED WITH WOOD CHIPS TO A DEPTH OF BETWEEN ONE AND TWO FEET IN THICKNESS. IT WAS RAINING AT THE TIME OF OUR INSPECTION, AND THE WOOD CHIP GROUNDCOVER WAS COMPLETELY WATERLOGGED, SITTING IN APPROXIMATELY HALF A FOOT OF WATER. THERE WERE DEEP RUTS IN THE WOOD CHIPS CAUSED BY EQUIPMENT OR VEHICLE TRAFFIC. ACCORDING TO GROWING POWER?S IEPA PERMIT APPLICATION, CONCRETE PAVING UNDERLIES THE WOOD CHIPS AND AN ONSITE STORM WATER SYSTEM COLLECTS AND DISCHARGES THE SITE?S RUNOFF TO THE CITY?S COMBINED SEWER SYSTEM. HOWEVER, BASED ON THE AMOUNT OF STANDING WATER AT THE TIME OF INSPECTION, IT APPEARED THAT THE ONSITE STORM WATER SYSTEM WASEITHER NOT FUNCTIONING PROPERLY OR DID NOT SERVE THE COMPOST AND ADJACENT AREAS. (BASED ON MIDWAY AIRPORT PRECIPITATION DATA, THE AREA RECEIVED 0.36' OF RAIN THE PREVIOUS DAY AND 1.51'BETWEEN AUGUST 1, 2013 AND AUGUST 22, 2013).


LAUREL SIMS INFORMED US THAT THEY HAD CONSTRUCTED A BERM ALONG THE SOUTH PORTION OF THE SITE TO PREVENT RUNOFF INTO BUBBLY CREEK. WE NOTIFIED MS. SIMS THAT SUCH CONSTRUCTION MAY REQUIRE A PERMIT FROM THE CITY AND THE ILLINOIS DEPARTMENT OF NATURAL RESOURCES IF THE PROPERTY IS WITHIN A FEDERAL SPECIAL FLOOD HAZARD AREA (SFHA). WE REQUESTED HER TO SEND US A TOPOGRAPHIC SURVEY OF THE SITE, IF AVAILABLE, SO THAT WE CAN CONFIRM THE FLOODPLAIN STATUS OF THE PROPERTY.(CDPHLATER CONFIRMED THE PROPERTY TO BEOUTSIDE THE SFHA. APPROXIMATE BASE FLOOD ELEVATION (BFE)FOR BUBBLY CREEK IS 583.68'.LOWEST ELEVATION OF THE TOP OF BANK (FROM APPENDIX E OF IEPA PERMIT APPLICATION) IS 586.00'.)


THE REMAINING AREAS OF THE SITE WERE BEING OPERATED AS AN URBAN

complaint_detail: CONSTRUCTION/DEMOLITION DEBRIS IN VACANT LOT AND ALLEY.
inspection_log: [INSPECTION LOG #:   ]

[INSPECTION LOG #: 10124 27-MAR-14 14:30:00] WENT TO SITE AT 228 W ILLINOIS AS PER REFERRAL ( VIA PHONE MESSAGE) FROM OSHA CALUMET OFFICE AND JIM MARTINICK ON WEDNESDAY3/26/2014. 

OSHA WAS THERE ON WEDNESDAY AND FOUND 25-30 BAGS OF PACM PIPE WRAP/ TSI IN THE BASEMENT OF A REHAB FORMER 1884 FIREHOUSE. AFTER ATTEMPTING TO GAIN ACCESS TO THE REAR OF THE PROPERTY FAILED, I INQUIRED IN THE CONSTRUCTION TRAILER LOCATION ON THE VACANT LOT TO THE WEST OF 228. THERE WERE SEVERAL PEOPLE IN THE TRAILER WHO DID NOT VOLUNTEER THEIR IDENTITY ONLY STATED THAT THEY HAD NO CONTACT OR CONNECTION WITH THE PROPERTY. I ASKED IF THERE WAS AN EMERGENCY NAME OR PHONE NUMBER AND THERE THEY ALL HAD NOTHING. I GAVE THEM MY CARD AND ASK IF THE REMEMBER ANYTHING TO CALL OR PASS ON MY INFORMATION TO CONTACT ME. OUTSIDE THERE WAS A MAN ADJUSTING THE FENCING AROUND THE WORK AREA. MILAN AS HE IDENTIFIED HIMSELF STATED THAT NO ONE WHO IN THE PROPERTY AND HE WAS A BRICKLAYER WHO WORKED FOR NABLA (INFORMATION ON FENCE PERMIT # 381955813 ADDRESS 1922 GEORGE CT GLENVIEW ILL 60025 CONTACT BISTRA KANGRGA 847-370-4553) NO WORKERS ON SITE AT THIS TIME. 

I PLACED A RETURN CALL TO OSHA WITH MY FINDINGS AND WAITED TO MAKE SURE NO WORKERS CAME OUT THE BACK FOR LUNCH. I RECEIVED A PHONE CALL FROM BRAD TOMS STATING THAT HE WOULD HAVE SOMEONE MEET ME ON SITE IN 15 MINUTES IF I WAS STILL AVAILABLE. AS I CALLED BACK THE OWNER FRED S LATSKO OF STRUCTURE DEVELOPMENT MIDWEST, LLC ARRIVED AND GREETED ME. HE HAD A WORKER (PETER) OPEN THE BACK DOOR AND REMOVE THE PLYWOOD ON THE DOOR TO THE BASEMENT AREA. I DONNED MY PPE AND FOLLOWED MR. LATSKO DOWN THE STAIR TO THE BASEMENT AREA. AT THE FOOT OF THE STAIRS, THERE WERE APPROXIMATELY 20 BLACK BAGS NEATLY ARRANGED. EACH BAG WAS FULL, NOT SEALED AND CONTAINED DRY TSI. THERE WAS PACM DEBRIS ON THE CLAY / DIRT GROUND AND 95% OF THE PIPES ON THE CEILING WERE STRIPPED OF THE MATERIAL. THE WAS MATERIAL ON THE PIPES BY THE BOILER AND ON THE GROUND AROUND IT, I ASKED MR LATSKO WHO REMOVED THE MATERIAL AND HE STATED THAT IT MIGHT HAVE BEEN SCRAPPERS WHO BROKE IN AND TOOK THE ACM OFF THE PIPES. BUT THE PIPES WERE STILL ON THE CEILING. HE STATED THAT THE BUILDING HAD BEEN DONATED TO LANDMARKS AND HE HAD GOTTEN IT FROM THE OWNERS ACROSS THE STREET GENE  GEORGETTI?S. HE ALSO STATED HE WAS NOT SURE WHY THE BANK WOULD HAVE GIVEN HIM A LOAN WITH ASBESTOS AND ENVIRONMENTAL ISSUES. 

THERE WAS EVIDENCE THAT WORKERS WERE INSIDE AND MR. LATSKO STATED THAT THERE WAS WORKER DIGGING FOR AN ELEVATOR PIT BUT NO ONE TOUCHED THE PIPES. THE BUILDING IS APPROX. 90 FT LONG X 30 FT WIDE. 

I TOOK THREE SAMPLES OF THE SUSPECT MATERIALS. FIRST SAMPLE WAS FROM THE BAGS DIRECTLY. 2ND FROM THE BOILER DEBRIS AND THE LAST FROM THE GROUND BY THE BOILER. I TOOK THE SAMPLES TO STAT LABS FOR ANALYSIS (PHOTOS AND RESULT ATTACHED IN REPORT SHOW THE SAMPLES WERE ALL THREE POSITIVE FOR ASBESTOS CONTAINING MATERIAL?S.) WE LEFT THE AREA AFTER TAKING PHOTOS AND DATA. THE WORKER PETER REATTCCHED THE PLY

complaint_detail: THE FUMES WERE COMING FROM THE FIRST FLOOR/CONSTRUCTION WORKSITE IN THE BLDG. NO WORKING VENTILATION SYSTEM IN THE BUILDING. SEVERAL PEOPLE IN OTHER PARTS OF THE BUILDING REPORTED HEADACHES, DIZZINESS AND NAUSEA YESTERDAY IN MID-AFTERNOON.
inspection_log: [INSPECTION LOG #: 360482 25-MAR-16 16:00:00] ON MARCH 25, 2016, AN ALDERMANIC COMPLAINT WAS RECEIVED CONCERNING VENTILATION ISSUES AND POSSIBLE CHEMICAL RELEASE/EXPOSURE ISSUES AT THE MEDICAL ARTS BUILDING, 1945 W. WILSON, CHICAGO, IL. THE RESPONDING INSPECTOR MET WITH TWO PHYSICIANS AND SUPPORT STAFFTWITHIN THE BUILDING. ADDITIONALLY, THE REPORTING INSPECTOR MET WITH THE SITE MAINTENANCE FOREMAN AND TELEPHONICALLY SPOKE WITH THE BUILDING'S GENERAL MANAGER. TWO ISSUES EXIST AT THIS FACILITY: THE HEATING AND VENTILATION SYSTEM (HVAC) IS RECEIVING AN UPGRADE, AND CURRENTLY NO BLOWERS ARE ACTIVELY ON LINE. THE HVAC SYSTEM IS BEING PASSIVELY MANIPULATED BY THE MAINTENANCE FOREMAN, WHO IS ATTEMPTING TO REGULATE THE SIX STORY STRUCTURE UNIT-BY-UNIT, WHILE NEW BLOWERS ARE BEING MANUFACTURED. TIME FRAME FOR NEW BLOWER UNITS IS APPROXIMATELY 30 DAYS. THE SECOND ISSUE AT THIS BUILDING WAS THE RELEASE OF CHEMICAL FUMES WHILE PREPARING A FLOOR FOR TILING. ON MARCH 23, 2016, TENANTS, PATIENTS AND OFFICE STAFF BECAME ILL FROM ODORS PRODUCED WHEN WORKERS IN A SUITE UNDERGOING RENOVATION ALLEGEDLY USED A COMPUND TO SEAL THE FLOOR PRIOR TO TILING. TENANTS CONTACTED BUILDING MANAGEMENT AND THE ALDERMAN'S OFFICE WHEN INDIVIDUALS BECAME ILL FROM ODORS COMING FROM THE SUITEUNDER RENOVATION. STAFF AT THE REHABILITATION INSTITUTE OF CHICAGO (RIC), LOCATED ACROSS THE HALL FROM THERENOVATION SUITE STATED THAT THEY MADE OBSERVATIONS OF THE COMPUND IN USE, AND IDENTIFIED IT AS POLYCOAT GL, PARTS AB.RIC OFFICIALS STATED THAT NO ONE WAS TAKEN TO AREA HOSPITALS, BUT THE ODOR REMAINED FOR AN EXTENDED PERIOD OF TIME. THE REPORTING INSPECTOR INTERVIEWED THE MAINTENANCE FOREMAN WHO STATED THAT HE ATTEMPTED TO HAVE THE FLOOR LABORERS OPEN THE SERIES OF WINDOWS IN THE SUITE, AND HE WAS TOLD BY THEM THAT THEY WOULD NOT OPEN THE WINDOWS OR VENTILATE TO THE OUTDOORS. THE REPORTING INSPECTOR THEN CONTACTED THE BUILDING'S SUPERINTENDENT, AND INFORMED HER OF HIS FINDINGS. THE SUPERINTENDENT WAS INFORMED THAT BASED UPON THE INFORMATION OBTAINED, IF ANOTHERINCIDENT HAPPENS DURING THE RENOVATION, THE BUILDING WILL BE EVACUATED. THE SUPERINTENDENT STATED THAT SHE IS AWARE OF THE SEVERITY OF THE ISSUE, AND CHANGES WILL BE MADE FOR REMODELING ACTIVITIES WITHIN THEBUILDING. THE REPORTING INSPECTOR FORWARED THE HVAC ISSUES TO EHT CHICAGO BUILDING DEPARTMENT FOR REVIEW OF THE HVAC SYSTEM, AND AN INSPECTION OF THE BUILDING'S HVAC SYSTEM WILL BE COMPLETED WITHIN THE NEXT FEW DAYS.

complaint_detail: CALLED COMPLAINANT CLAIRE COLEMAN 773 818-9634 TO ASK WHEN SHE COULD OCCUPY HER SIDE OF A DUPLEX THAT HAS RECENTLY HAD ASBESTOS ABATEMENT WORK BEING DONE. SHE HAS BEEN DISPLACED SINCE APRIL.
inspection_log:
[INSPECTION LOG #: 1055507 27-JUN-16 12:45:00] I CALLED THE COMPLAINANT, MS. CLAIRE COLEMAN PRIOR TO ARRIVING AT THE RESIDENCE TO GAIN ACCESS TO THE UNIT FOR INSPECTION. I LEFT A MESSAGE AND PROCEEDED TO THE LOCATION. WHEN I ARRIVED AT THE CONDO BUILDING, I CONTACTED THE MANAGEMENT COMPANY AND MET WITH MS. GINA DAVIS WHO IS THE CONDO BOARD'S SECRETARY. MS. DAVIS STATED THAT THE CONDO WAS PURCHASED AS IS BY MS. COLEMAN IN DECEMBER 2015. SHE ALSO STATED THE UNIT 6N HADBEEN VACANT FOR SEVERAL YEARS PRIORTO SELL.SHE DID NOT HAVE KEYS TO THE UNIT FOR INSPECTION. 

I REACHED OUT TO MS. COLEMAN VIA THE INTERCOM SYSTEM (GOES TO HER CELL)AND EXPLAINED THE REASON FOR THE INSPECTION. MS. COLEMAN STATED SHE WOULD BE ABLE TO GET THERE IS 30 MINUTES. WHEN SHE ARRIVEDI INSPECTEDHER UNIT.MS. COLEMAN STATED THAT SHE HAD A BLOCKAGE IN HER KITCHEN SINK AND SHE OR A PLUMBER REMOVED AN APPROXIMATE 2 X 3 FOOT SECTION OF THE ADJOINING WALL IN THE LIVING ROOM TO EXPOSE THE PLUMBING PIPE CHASE. THERE WAS ONE OLD STEAM PIPE IN THE CHASE THAT HAD PACM WRAP AND 3 INCH SECTION WAS SLIGHTLY DAMAGED TOWARDS THE BOTTOM OF THE OPENING. THE BUILDING,APPROXIMATELY 100 YEARS OLD WITH 14 CONDO UNITS,WAS FORMALLY HEATED BY RADIATOR AND STEAM HEAT BUT EACH UNIT HAS THEIR OWN SEPARATE HEAT SYSTEM CURRENTLY. I SUGGESTED TO MS COLEMAN, THE CONDO OWNER, THAT SHE SHOULD HIRE A LICENSED ABATEMENT COMPANY TO REPAIR OR REMOVE THE SMALL SECTION SO THE PLUMBERS CAN CONTINUE THE REPAIRS. I RECOMMEND THAT MS COLEMAN CONTACTS A COMPANY AS SOON AS POSSIBLE AND THAT SHE FORWARDS THE ABATEMENT COMPANY REPAIR PAPERWORK TO ME.

ON THE SECOND ISSUE OF ACM BUILDING MAINTENANCE, WHEN I MEET WITH MS DAVIS AND MS MCALLISTER OF THE CONDO BOARD,I ASKED TO INSPECT THE COMMON AREAS WHILE I WAITED FORMS. COLEMAN TO ARRIVE.WHILE CONDUCTING MY INSPECTION OF THE COMMON AREAS BOILER AND LAUNDRY ROOMS, I FOUND A 3 FOOT LENGTH OF PACM PIPE RISER NEAR THE REAR DOOR THAT HAD3 INCHES OF EXPOSED PIPE WRAP BY THE RADIATOR. THE LAUNDRY ROOMS ALSO HAD PACM PIPE WRAP THAT WAS IN GOOD CONDITION. THEPIPE ENDS NEEDED TO PATCHED OR REPAIRED.THE BOILER ROOM IS CLEAN AND OUT OF COMMISSION.I EXPLAINED TO THEBOARD REPSTHAT THE BUILDING IS RESPONSIBLE TO MAINTAIN ANY ACM IN THE COMMON AREASINA NON DAMAGED / NON FRIABLE CONDITION. I EXPLAINED THE CITY OF CHICAGO MUNICIPAL ORDINANCE 11-4-2180 A TO THEM.BEFORE LEAVING THE SITE, I REITERATED THE BOARDREPSTHE NEED TO REPAIR OR REMOVE THE DAMAGED TSI IN THE COMMON AREAS OF THE BUILDING BEFORE FRIDAY JULY 1, 2016. A FOLLOW UP EMAIL WAS SENT TO ALSO INCLUDE AIR CLEARANCE IN THE COMMON AREAS FOR REASSURANCE TO THERESIDENTS THERE IS NOASBESTOS FIBERS REMAINING. THEY ARE AWARE THAT IF THERE IS LACK OF COOPERATION WITH THE MAINTENANCE A NOV WILL BE ISSUED THEREAFTER.

FURTHER COMMUNICATIONS AND POSSIBLE FOLLOW UP INSPECTIONS MAY BE REQUIRED TO SHOW COMPLIANCE WITH THE SUGGESTED OM WORK.

complaint_detail: CITY OF CHICAGO BUILDING EMPLOYEES WORRIED ASBESTOS WALLS IN THROUGHOUT THE 3RD FLOOR HAVE BEEN PEELING AND BUBBLING APART.
inspection_log:
[INSPECTION LOG #: 1473012 26-AUG-16 10:30:00] I WENT TO INVESTIGATE AN ANONYMOUS COMPLAINT AT THE LOCATION OF A CITY OF CHICAGO STREET AND SANITATION (SS) OFFICE FACILITY. THE CONCERNS WERE OF BUBBLING AND PEELING PAINT ON THE 3RD FLOOR AND CONCERNS IT WAS ASBESTOS CONTAINING MATERIALS. WHEN I ARRIVED, I MET A SS SUPERVISORJOHN ZIFRON.IEXPLAINED TO HIM THE NATURE OF MY VISIT ANDASKED IF HE WAS AWARE OF ANY AREASTHAT WERE SPECIFIC TO LOOK AT.MR. ZIFRON STATED THAT HE WAS NOT AWARE OF ANY ISSUES BUT I WAS FREE TO INSPECT ANY PARTOF THE PROPERTYAND IFI NEEDED HELPWITHACCESSING ANY ROOMS HE COULD HELP.

I CONTINUED UP TO THE 2ND AND3RD FLOORS OF THIS OLDER BRICK PROPERTY.I FOUNDA WATER LEAK IN THE WOMEN'S BATHROOM ON THE 2ND FLOOR. THERE WERESEVERAL AREAS UNDER WINDOW SILLS IN THE STAIRWELL TO THE 3 FLOOR WHERE WATER OR MOISTURE HAD PENETRATED THE PLASTER UNDER THE WINDOWS AND IS CAUSING THE PAINT TO PEEL AND BUBBLE.ON MY WAY UP THE STAIRSTO THE 3 FLOOR SOUTHEND OF THE BUILDING, I MEETAN EMPLOYEE FROM2FM. JESSE DIAZ IS THE PROPERTIESBUILDING ENGINEER. IASKEDMR.DIAZ IF HE WAS AWARE OF ANY ISSUES WITH WALLS PEELING AND BUBBLING. HE SAID THATTHERE IS APROBLEM IN THE DEPUTY COMMISSIONERS OFFICE AND NORTHCONFERENCE ROOM ON THE 3RD FLOOR. WE MEETWITHDEPUTY COMMISSIONER MR. WHITESIDE FROM THE BUREAU OF FORESTRY IN HIS OFFICE ON THE 3RD FLOOR. I EXPLAINED THE COMPLAINANT'S CONCERNS AND THAT IF THERE IS NO ASBESTOS ISSUES, THE COMPLAINT WAS TO BE REFERRED TO 2FM FOR REPAIR WORK ORDERS. HE STATED THAT HE HAD SPOKEN TO JULIEWITH 2FM TO HAVE THE AREAS LOOKED AT. MR. WHITESIDE SHOWED US HIS OFFICE AND THE ADJACENT CONFERENCE ROOM. MR. WHITESIDE STATED THAT THIS PROPERTY WAS RENOVATED APPROXIMATELY 9 YEARS AGO AND IT IS A GREEN LEADS PROPERTY. FORESTRY WAS MOVED TO THIS FACILITY FROM 31ST AND KEDZIE BUILDING AT THAT TIME.

IN THE 3ROOMS,THE NORTH AND WEST WALLS ABOVE AND ALONG THE NEWERWINDOWS APPEARED TO HAVE HADCONDENSATION MOISTURE BUILD UPOR WATEREXPOSURE. THE PLASTER SKIM COATING AND PAINT WAS BECOMING CALCIFIED FROM THIS MOISTURE OVER TIME. THE PLASTER HAS BECOME WHITE CHALKY ANDPOWDERY. THISAPPEARANCE THAT IS OFTEN MISTAKEN FOR ASBESTOS CONTAINING MATERIALS. THE AREAS IN THESES ROOMSWERE NOT VISIBLY WET BUT THE CONFERENCE ROOM WAS EXTREMELY COLD FROM AIR CONDENSER AND COLD AIR VENTS.

NOTE:THERE WAS NO VISIBLE MOLD GROWTH OR WET ODOR IN THESELOCATIONS INSPECTED AT THIS TIME.

MR. DIAZ STATED THAT HE WAS AWARE OF A LEAKING FROM THE ROOF AND A WORK ORDER WAS PLACED FOR THAT REPAIR. TUCK POINTING OF THEEXTERIOR BRICKS ANDCAULKINGAROUND THEWINDOWS MIGHT HELP TO CORRECT THEISSUE.MR. DIAZ AND I AGREED THAT THE MOISTURE / WATER LEAK INFILTRATION NEEDS TO FOUND AND STOPPED BEFORE THE INTERIOR REPAIRS ARE COMPLETED. 

THE FINDINGS OF THIS COMPLAINT WILL BE REFERRED TO FLEET AND FACILITIES MANAGEMENT (2FM) FOR FURTHER WORK ORDER TO REPAIR THE ISSUES. NO FURTHER INSPECTION IS NEEDED. COMPLAINT UNFOUNDED AND INVALID. REFERRED AND CLOSED.

complaint_detail: 1ST FLOOR AREA REAR BY FREIGHT ELEVATOR BY LAUNDRY ROOM WORKERS WERE REMOVING FLOOR TILES. CALLERS STATES THAT THERE WAS NO PROTECTION FOR THIS ASBESTOS FLOORING BEING USED BY WORKERS AND DUST ALL OVER THE AREA.
inspection_log: [INSPECTION LOG #: 1734417 06-OCT-16 11:30:00] I WAS ASSIGNED A COMPLAINT TO INVESTIGATE CONCERNS OF WORKERS REMOVING TILE FROM THE REAR HALLWAY IN THIS RESIDENTIAL APARTMENT PROPERTY. CALLER STATED THE WORK WAS ON THE 1ST FLOOR AREA IN THEREAR BY FREIGHT ELEVATOR AND BY LAUNDRY ROOM. CALLERS STATES THAT THERE WAS NO PROTECTION BEING USED BY WORKERS AND DUST ALL OVER THE AREA. WHEN I ARRIVED I ENTERED THE PROPERTY THROUGH THE REAR SERVICE DOOR IN THE COURTYARD. THE GARBAGE ROOM LEAD DIRECTLY TO THE HALLWAY BY THE LAUNDRY ROOM. THERE WERE NO WORKERS REMOVING TILE AT THIS TIME AND THE TILE APPEARED TO BEALL INSTALLED NEWERVINYL 12 X 12 TILES (SEE PHOTOS) THERE WERE 2 CUSTODIAL WORKERS MOPPING THE FLOOR AND DID NOT KNOW ABOUT THE WORK WHEN I QUESTIONED THEM. I LOOKED AROUND THE REST OF THE HALLWAY, OPENING DOORS AND GOING TO THE BASEMENT AND STAIRWAYS.THE STAIRS AND THE OTHER FLOORS WERE PAINTED CONCRETE.THE BUILDING IS A COURTYARD 2 TOWERED STRUCTURE WITH 2 ENTRANCES( NORTH AND SOUTH). I INSPECTED BOTH FOYER AREAS WHICH HAD LARGE SCALE TILE FLOORS (SEE PHOTOS). IN THE BATHROOMS AND LAUNDRY ROOM THE FLOORING WAS CERAMIC TILES. I FOUND NO SIGNS OF ANY OTHER TYPES OF POSSIBLE ASBESTOS CONTAINING MATERIALS OR VINYL ASBESTOS TILE IN THE COMMON OR BASEMENT AREAS. I WENT TO THE MANAGEMENT OFFICE LOCATED IN THE NORTH TOWER AND SPOKE TO ME THE ASSISTANT PROPERTY MANAGER MS NATASHA ROBISON. I ASKED HER IF SHE KNEW WHEN THE REPLACEMENT TILE WORK WAS DONE. SHE STATED THAT THE WORK WAS DONE FROM SEPTEMBER 27 TO 30, 2016. I ASKED FOR THE CONTRACTOR INFORMATION. SHE GAVE ME THE INFORMATION FOR A CD CONSTRUCTION LLC AND PHONE NUMBER. I ATTEMPTED TO CONTACT THE COMPANY SEVERAL TIMES AND WAS NOT ABLE TO LEAVE A MESSAGE CAUSE THE VOICE MAIL BOX WAS FULL. I ASKED HER IF THE PROPERTY HAD ANY ANALYTICAL TESTINGFOR SAMPLING OF THE TILE THAT WAS REMOVED, IF ANY. SHE STATED THAT THE REGIONAL MANAGER WOULD KNOWTHAT INFORMATION. SHE DID NOT KNOW IF THERE WAS TILE REMOVED BUT ONLY NEW TILE LAID. SHE GAVE ME THE INFORMATION TO CALL THE CORPORATE OFFICES FOR TLC MANAGEMENT COMPANYDOWNTOWN CHICAGO ON 100 S LASALLE.I CALLED AND LEFT A MESSAGE WITH MS. PASSION STIRGUS. I AM WAITING A RETURN CALL. I CONTACTED THE COMPLAINANT TO LET HIM KNOWTHAT THE CITY WAS INVOLVED AND WAS INVESTIGATING THE WORK THAT IS COMPLETED. I EXPLAINED THAT I CONTACTED THE MANAGEMENTOFFICES AND THANKED HIM FOR CONTACTING 311. THE COMPLAINT WAS UNFOUNDED BUT WILL ADD ON WHEN I HEAR BACK FROM TLC.

complaint_detail: CONSTRUCTION CREW DUMPED SOIL FROM 5628 TO 5632.
inspection_log: [INSPECTION LOG #: 2273979 20-JAN-17 12:05:00] ON JANUARY 20, 2017, CITY OF CHICAGO DEPARTMENT OF PUBLIC HEALTH INSPECTOR JOHN SINGLER RESPONDED TO A COMPLAINT AT 5632 N. KEYSTONE AVE., CHICAGO, IL. THE RESIDENCE AT THE COMPLAINT ADDRESS IS AT THE STAGE OF A FRAMESHELLFOR A NEW DWELLING. THE REPORTING INSPECTOR WROTE A CITATION TO THE PROPERTY DEVELOPER FOR AN UNRELATED MATTER THAT IS PENDING. THE REPORTING INSPECTOR MET WITH THE COMPLAINANT WHO STATED THAT EXCESS MUD AND SOIL FROM CONSTRUCTION WORK IS NOT BEING HANDLED IN A PROPER MANNER. MUD AND CLAY REMNANTS WERE VISIBLE IN THE STREET AND ON THE SIDEWALK, BUT THREE WORKERS WERE SCRAPING THE DEBRIS UPON THE INSPECTOR'S ARRIVAL. COLEMAN MCDONOUGH, MC DONOUGH PLUMBING (773) 330-2473, STATED THAT HIS CREW CREATED THE MUD DURING THE RECONFIGURING OF THE PLUMBING TO THE CITY'S WATER LINE. MC DONOUGH STATED THAT THE MUD ISDIFFICULT TO MANAGE WITH CHICAGO'S DAILY RAINS, DOCUMENTED ASRAIN DURING THE PREVIOUSSIX DAYS. MC DONOUGH WAS TOLD THAT EVEN THOUGH WEATHER WAS A PRIMARYFACTOR, MUD AND CLAY NEEDED TO BE SWEPT A NUMBER OF TIMES A DAY. MC DONOUGH STATED THAT THE CREWS WOULD CONTINUE TO MONITOR AND SWEEP THE MUD AND CLAY. THE COMPLAINANT WAS INFORMED THAT REASONABLE EFFORTS WERE BEING MADE TO MANAGE THE SITUATION, AND A CITATION WOULD BE WRITTEN IF CONDITIONS WORSEN. THIS INSPECTION IS CLOSED.

complaint_detail: SMOKE IS COMING FROM FACILITY INSIDE OF THE PHONE STORE INDOORS.
inspection_log: [INSPECTION LOG #: 3155588 06-JUN-17 13:35:00] CDPH ENGINEER (BOB S.) CONDUCTED CITIZEN'S AIR POLLUTION COMPLAINT INVESTIGATION. UPON ARRIVAL - AREA WAS CANVASSED FROM E 79TH ST, THE ALLEY AND S. JEFFERY ST. THERE WAS A MARGINAL BBQ ODOR DETECTED AT THE ALLEY AND MARGINAL WHITE SMOKE DISCHARGED FROM THE ROOF. BOB CIRCLED THE AREA AND STOPPED AT THE ALLEY, OBSERVING THE VISIBLE STACK (SEE THE IMAGE). AT HE ALLEY BOB MET THE MANAGER - RICK B.MGR. BOTH GENTLEMAN MET BEFORE, WHEN BOB WAS INVESTIGATING FIRST COMPLAINT. RICK MENTIONED ABOUT A RECENT FIRE OF THE BUILDING AND ABOUT ROOF TO BE FIXED, AS WELL THESTRUCTURE REPAIR WHICH WILL START ON AUG 15, 2017. NEXT BOB AND RICK WALKED INSIDE THE KITCHEN (SEE IMAGES), WHERE BOB NOTICED THE COOKING HOOD WITH GREASE FILTERS EXHAUSTING THE BBQ WOOD CHIPS FIRED - GRILLING THE CHICKEN PIECES. THERE WAS SOME SMOKE ACCUMULATED INSIDE THE KITCHEN. BOB VERIFIED VALID LICENSE CERTIFICATE (IMAGED). RICK WAS ADVISED, THAT ONLY REASONABLE METHOD TO SUPPRESS THE SMOKE WOULD BE REDUCTION AMOUNT OF THE WOOD CHIPS USED TO MAINTAIN THE TEMPERATURE (350 F) AND ADDING THE FLAVOR TO THE GRILLED CHICKEN. ALSO BBQ UNIT WILL HAVE TO ADD GAS FIRED BURNERS (FOR NG OR PROPANE). AFTER MODIFICATIONS AND CONSTRUCTION REPAIRSTO THE STRUCTURE, PASSING DOB AND VENT INSPECTIONS THE BANANA LEAF RESTAURANT MUST APPLY FOR APCP FOR BBQ GRILL AND COOKING HOOD. AT EXISTING SITUATION APCP WOULD BE DENIED. DUE TO PARTIALLY ELIMINATETHE POTENTIAL SMOKE AND ODOR RICK AGREED TO MINIMIZE THE USAGE OF WOODEN CHIPS. CDPH WILL BE CALLED FOR THE RE-INSPECTION. NO NOV WAS ISSUED AT THIS TIME, YET. IF FACILITY WILL NOT COMPLY IN 90 DAYS CDPH ON BEHALF OF DOBMAY RECOMMEND TOCEASE THE OPERATION OF THIS BUSINESS. THIS CASE WAS ALSO FORWARDED TO DOB, TO EVALUATE THE SAFETY OF THE STRUCTURE AND AIR EXCHANGE.

complaint_detail: CONSTRUCTION SITE HAVE DAMAGE CAUSED AND HAS SAID MORE BRICKS HAVE FALLEN FROM THE CREWS PROJECT.
inspection_log: [INSPECTION LOG #: 3649325 07-AUG-17 12:15:00] ON AUGUST 7, 2017 CITY OF CHICAGO DEPARTMENT OF PUBLIC HEALTH (CDPH) INSPECTOR JOHN SINGLER RESPONDED TO AN ALDERMANICCOMPLAINT AT 1325 N. WELLS ST., CHICAGO, IL.A NEW DEVELOPMENT IS BEING BUILT BY ALPHA CONSTRUCTION SERVICES (ACS). THE REPORTING INSPECTOR RESPONDED TO COMPLAINTS AT THE SITE TWO TIMES PREVIOUSLY; IN APRIL AND JULY 2017 ANDDURING THOSE INSPECTIONSDISCUSSIONS WERE HELD WITH THE SUPERINTENDENT AND IMPROVEMENTS WERE MADE. ON THIS DATE THE REPORTING INSPECTOR MET WITH THE OWNER OF A CUSTOM AUTOCENTER TO THE SOUTH OF THE NEW DEVELOPMENT. THEBUSINESS OWNER STATED THAT THERE HAVE BEEN CONSTRUCTION PROBLEMS WITH THE DEVELOPMENTSINCE THE PROJECT BEGAN ANDNOW HE WANTED TO DISCUSS AIR VIOLATIONS. AS THE DISCUSSION WAS BEING HELD, WATER SPRAY FROM PRESSURE WASHING AND MORTAR MIX FROM BRICK LAYING WAFTED ACROSS THE NEIGHBORING PROPERTY ON TO THE VEHICLES AND PARTIES PRESENT.THE PRESSURE WASH OVERSPRAY AND MORTAR MIX FELL ON TO WELLS STREET AND THE SIDEWALK AREAIN THREE DIRECTIONS. IN THE BACK OF THE DEVELOPMENT DUST WAS BEING KICKED UP IN THE ALLEY FROM THE DEVELOPMENT, WHERE WATER WAS NOT BEING APPLIED TO REDUCE THE DUST FROM THE CONSTRUCTION SITE. MESHING THAT HAD PREVIOUSLY BEEN PRESENT ACROSS THE FRONT OF THE PROPERTYHAD BEENREMOVED. THE COMPLAINANTPRODUCED BRICK FRAGMENTS THAT HE STATED HIT HIS SON FROM THE FOURTH FLOOR OF THE NEW DEVELOPMENT DURING BRICK LAYING. THE REPORTING INSPECTOR MET WITH AN INDIVIDUAL WHO STATED THAT HE WASACTING FOR THE ACS SUPERINTENDENT, WHO WAS ON VACATION. THE REPORTING INSPECTOR ASKED IF A CHEMICAL WAS BEING USED TO PRESSURE WASH THE BUILDING. THE ACTING SUPERVISORSTATED 'YES.' A TELEPHONE CALL WAS PLACED BY THE ACTING SUPERVISORTO THE PRESSURE WASHING TEAM WHO WERE ON SCAFFOLDING, AND THE FOREMAN OF THE TEAM HELD UP A PAIL OF 'NMD80.' NO ARCHITECTURAL SURFACE CLEANING PERMIT (PRESSURE WASH PERMIT) IS IN PLACE FOR THE PROJECT.THEPRESSURE WASH FOREMAN STATED THAT THENMD80 WASTHE 'SAFEST MATERIAL ON THE MARKET.' (SEE ATTACHED PHOTOS AND MSDS SHEETS). THE ACTING SUPERVISOR WAS ASKED WHY ALL OF THE MESHING, EXCEPT FOR AN ADVERTISEMENT, WAS REMOVED FROM THE CONSTRUCTION SITE. HE STATED THAT HE DID NOT KNOW THE REASON. THE ACTING SUPERVISOR WAS INFORMED THAT CITATIONS WERE BEING WRITTEN AND THE CONDITION OF THE PROPERTY WAS UNACCEPTABLE. THE ACTING SUPERVISOR STATED THAT THE SUPERINTENDENT WOULD RETURN FROM VACATION IN THREE DAYS. THREE CITATIONS WERE SERVED VIA U.S. MAIL ON ACS: CITATION E00003224610, SANDBLASTING, GRINDING, CHEMICAL WASHING, 11-4-2190(A) PERMIT. CITATION E00003224417, CONSTRUCTION SITE CLEANLINESS, 13-32-125(2)(C) FENCE MESHING, AND 13-32-125(K), DUST ON PUBLIC WAY. CITATION E00003224518, NUISANCE IN CONNECTION WITHA BUSINESS 7-28-080 FAILURE TO CONTROL FALLING DEBRIS. THE CITATIONS WERE MAILED TO THE ACS REGISTERED AGENT ALSO OF THE SAME ADDRESS AS ACS, 1525 W. HOMER SUITE 401, CHICAGO, IL 60642. HEARING DATE SEPTEMBER 14, 2017.

complaint_detail: IMPROPER DISPOSAL OF SOLID AND LIQUID WASTE.
inspection_log:
[INSPECTION LOG #: 4440456 15-NOV-17 12:30:00] IN REQUEST OF THE 16TH WARD OFFICE A TEAM OF CITY DEPARTMENTAL TASK FORCE CONDUCTED A TOUR INVESTIGATION OF THE WARD SELECTED FACILITIES TO DETERMINE COMPLIANCE WITH CITY  STATE REGULATIONS. 

UPON ARRIVAL AT ONE OF THE SITES C  H TRUCK  AUTO REPAIR, INC. LOCATED AT 1334 W 59TH ST. I PROCEEDED TO THE OFFICE AND INTRODUCED MYSELF. I STATED THE PURPOSE OF MY VISIT AND REQUESTED A WALKTHROUGH OF THE FACILITY WITH THE MANAGER.

THE FACILITY ENGAGES IN MOTOR VEHICLE REPAIR, EXCLUSIVELY HEAVY DUTY TRUCKS, TRAILERS, AND TRACTORS. FACILITY IS NOT AN AUTO BODY REFINISHER AND NO SPRAY BOOTH WAS FOUND. 

AT THE TIME OF INSPECTION I OBSERVED DIFFERENT SIZES OF WASTE OIL AND ANTIFREEZE CONTAINERS FILLED WITH LIQUID WASTE. 

THERE WERE ABOUT 3 LARGE PLASTIC TANKS FILLED WITH SEVERAL HUNDRED GALLONS OF AUTOMOTIVE LIQUID WASTE SPILLING OIL ON THE GROUND, ITOLD THE MANAGER IT APPEARS LIKE EVERYWHERE YOU LOOK IN THE SHOP WAS OIL BECAUSE OF POOR MANAGEMENT OF WASTE OIL. 

I INSTRUCTED THE MANAGER TO PLACE THE DRUMS AND THE CONTAINERSIN SECONDARY CONTAINMENTS TO PREVENT SPILL. I INQUIRED OF WHICH COMPANY WAS CONTRACTED TO PICK UP THE WASTE OIL FOR DISPOSAL HE REPLIED NONE BECAUSE HE BURNS IT FOR HEAT. 

I SAW A CATCH BASIN IN THE MIDDLE OF THE SHOP FILLED WITH MIXTURE OF WATER AND A LITTLE OIL SHINE 

DURING MY EXIT INTERVIEW I WARNED THE MANAGER MR. ENOC HERNANDEZ TO PRACTICE GOOD HOUSEKEEPING AND TO DISPOSE HIS WASTE PROPERLY WITH SOME OFFICIAL WASTE DISPOSAL COMPANIES. 

I INFORMED HIM THAT FACILITY WAS FOUND IN VIOLATION OF CITY CODE 11-4-1500 TREATMENT AND DISPOSAL OF SOLID OR LIQUID WASTE. 

NOTICE OF VIOLATION E000032432 16 WAS ISSUED.

COURT DATE IS SCHEDULED FOR 01-11-2018 AT 400 W SUPERIOR ROOM 112 @ 01:00PM

complaint_detail: ILLEGAL DUMPING WASTE AT ABOVE LOCATION.
inspection_log:
[INSPECTION LOG #: 4781587 11-JAN-18 12:44:00]

THE NAME ON THE TAG WAS NOT MUCH HELP TO CONTACT THE OWNER/OWNERS AS I INTEND TO NOTIFY THE OWNER/OWNERS THAT THEY WERE FOUND IN ALLEGED VIOLATIONS OF CITY MUNICIPAL CODES. 

AFTER A TITLE SEARCH AT THE COOK COUNTY TREASURER'S OFFICE I FOUND THE COOK COUNTY PROPERTY TAX AND PAYMENT INFORMATION FOR PROPERTY INDEX NUMBER [PIN] 16-13-205-041-0000 TAX YEAR 2017 PAYABLE IN 2018,MAILING INFORMATION DDS REALTY LP. 1658 N MILWAUKEE # 335 CHICAGO IL 60647. 

AFTERTHE TITLE SEARCH THOSE PERSON/PERSONS RESPONSIBLE FOR WASTE REMOVAL 11-4-1585(A) AND TREATMENT AND DISPOSAL OF SOLID OR LIQUID WASTE: 11-4-1500. AT THE ABOVE ADDRESS WERE FOUND IN VIOLATION OF CITY CODES.

complaint_detail: CSR# 18-01059112 WORKERS DIGGING IN FLU ASH WITHOUT ANY PERSONAL PROTECTION. NO WATER IN USE TO DEPRESS DUST.
inspection_log: [INSPECTION LOG #: 5326851 29-MAR-18 14:00:00] ON MARCH 29, 2018 CITY OF CHICAGO DEPARTMENT OF PUBLIC HEALTH (CDPH) INSPECTOR JOHN SINGLER RESPONDED TO A COMPLAINT CONCERNING AIRBORNE DUST AT THE BEEMSTERBOER STORAGE FACILITY LOCATED AT 2800 E. 106TH ST., CHICAGO, IL. THE FACILITY CONTAINS FLU DUST FROM INDUSTRIAL PROCESSES, AND THE PILE HAD BEEN ACTIVELY REDUCED IN VOLUMEPRIOR TO THIS INSPECTION. DUE TO DUST CONTROL AND EMISSIONS CONCERNS, REMOVAL ACTIVITIES WERE HALTED THE PRIOR WEEK. THE PILE OF FLU DUST, WHICH RUNS EAST-TO-WEST ALONG 106TH ST., HAS BEEN COVERED WITH TARPING AND NO ACTIVITY WAS TAKING PLACE AT THE TIME OF THE INSPECTION. THE FRONT GATE WAS LOCKED AND THE FENCE IN FRONT OF THE GATE WAS LOCKED AND IS BLOCKED WITH A LARGE PIECE OF CONCRETE. HEAVY EQUIPMENT WAS PARKED ON SITE AND APPEARED TO BE IN THE SAME LOCATION AS DURINGPREVIOUS INSPECTIONS WHEN THE FACILITY WAS UNMANNED.INSPECTIONS CONTINUE UNDER VARIOUS INSPECTORS, BOTH FROM THEILLINOIS ENVIRONMENTAL PROTECTION AGENCY AND CDPH.
